(Medusae Controls Guide \(Detailed\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document explains every control shown in the settings panel for the Medusae renderer and) Tj
T*
(what each one changes visually.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Source locations used:) Tj
T*
(- src/data/settingsConfig.js \(controls shown in the UI\)) Tj
T*
(- packages/medusae/src/defaults.js \(default values\)) Tj
T*
(- packages/medusae/src/Medusae.jsx \(actual behavior in shader + cursor follow logic\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Important distinction:) Tj
T*
(- Some controls change how far things move \(amplitude/strength\).) Tj
T*
(- Some controls change how fast things move \(frequency/speed/drag response\).) Tj
T*
(- Some controls change shape only \(width/height/size/color\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CURSOR CONTROLS) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1\) Hover Radius \(cursor.radius\)) Tj
T*
(What it does:) Tj
T*
(- Sets the radius of the cursor jitter orbit used when hovering. The cursor target is not) Tj
T*
(  perfectly still; it is animated with a small wobble around the actual pointer.) Tj
T*
(Visual effect:) Tj
T*
(- Higher values make the interaction zone wobble farther around the cursor.) Tj
T*
(- The particle field appears to swirl around a larger moving target.) Tj
T*
(What it does NOT do:) Tj
T*
(- It does not directly increase particle size.) Tj
T*
(- It does not directly increase response speed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2\) Hover Strength \(cursor.strength\)) Tj
T*
(What it does:) Tj
T*
(- Multiplies the jitter offset added around the cursor target.) Tj
T*
(Visual effect:) Tj
T*
(- Higher values make the hover motion more dramatic and energetic.) Tj
T*
(- The cursor influence point moves farther from the pointer during the wobble animation.) Tj
T*
(When to increase:) Tj
T*
(- If you want more expressive cursor motion without changing smoothing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3\) Drag Factor \(cursor.dragFactor\)) Tj
T*
(What it does:) Tj
T*
(- Controls how quickly the internal mouse uniform \(uMouse\) catches up to the target cursor) Tj
T*
(  position using interpolation.) Tj
T*
(- The code effectively does: current += \(target - current\) * dragFactor) Tj
T*
(Visual effect:) Tj
T*
(- Higher values = faster, snappier cursor tracking.) Tj
T*
(- Lower values = smoother, laggier, floatier follow behavior.) Tj
T*
(This is the main ?speed with cursor? control.) Tj
T*
(Typical tuning guidance:) Tj
T*
(- 0.01 to 0.02 = soft / delayed) Tj
ET
endstream
